Name: ovarian cystadenocarcinoma
Definition: An ovary adenocarcinoma that is characterized by the presence of cysts or cystic spaces.

Name: ovarian mucinous adenocarcinoma
Definition: An ovary adenocarcinoma that is characterized by the presence of mucin.

Name: rete ovarii adenocarcinoma
Definition: An ovary adenocarcinoma that arises from the rete ovarii.

Name: ovarian clear cell adenocarcinoma
Definition: A ovarian adenocarcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells which have clear cytoplasm.
Synonym: Clear cell carcinoma of the Cervix Uteri

Name: obsolete malignant ovarian clear cell neoplasm
Definition: A ovarian adenocarcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells which have clear cytoplasm.
Synonym: Clear cell carcinoma of the Cervix Uteri

Name: ovary serous adenocarcinoma
Definition: An ovary adenocarcinoma that derives_from the lining of a cavity that produces a serum-like fluid (a serous cavity).

Name: endometrioid ovary carcinoma
Definition: An ovary adenocarcinoma that has_material_basis_in endometrial tissue.
